    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The power diagram boundary formula for two sites p1 (weight w1) and p2 (weight w2) is the locus where d(x,p1)&sup2; - w1 = d(x,p2)&sup2; - w2. Expanding the squared distances, the quadratic terms cancel, leaving a linear equation: the boundary is a hyperplane. The shift from the Voronoi midpoint is (w2 - w1) / (2 * d(p1, p2)). The ad auction interpretation follows Edelman, Ostrovsky, and Schwarz (2007); the power diagram framing is a geometric restatement of their algebraic result.</p>

